title: Oracle Wallet + Vault DBSE PoC - HTTP/JWT credential flow

Oracle DB -> Oracle DB: Create app_user with initial password


Vault -> Oracle DB: Configure DBSE connection as SYSTEM
note  Vault: memory: ORACLE_PASSWORD and DBSE config

Vault -> Vault: Create DBSE static role app-user-wallet
note  Vault: role maps Vault DBSE role to Oracle user app_user

Vault -> Oracle DB: Rotate app_user password
note  Vault: memory: generated app_user password

Vault DBSE changes app_user password in Oracle

note Oracle DB: drive: Oracle stores authentication data for the new app_user password

Vault Agent -> Vault: Read database/static-creds/app-user-wallet
note  Vault Agent: Vault Agent reads current static credential from DBSE

Vault Agent -> Vault Agent: Start update-wallet.py with current credential
note  Vault Agent: memory: current DB username and password are injected as environment variables, rotation ID is injected with them

Vault Agent -> Vault Agent: Sign wallet update request
note  Vault Agent: The JWT is attached to the request as proof that Vault Agent authorized it.
The DB password is in the request body, not in the JWT.

Vault Agent -> Oracle DB Client: POST wallet update request
note  Vault Agent: memory: request carries current DB username, password, and rotation ID

Oracle DB Client -> Oracle DB Client: Authorize wallet update
note  Oracle DB Client: public key used to verify Vault Agent signatures
* accept only valid Vault Agent update requests

* reject expired requests or requests for another wallet alias

* reject if signed rotation ID differs from request rotation ID

Oracle DB Client -> Oracle Wallet Store: Remove old wallet credential
note  Oracle Wallet Store: existing credential for FREEPDB1_WALLET is removed if present

Oracle DB Client -> Oracle Wallet Store: Write new wallet credential
note  Oracle DB Client: memory: mkstore receives the current DB password
hardening: avoid passing DB password in process arguments
note  Oracle Wallet Store: drive: ewallet.p12 and cwallet.sso contain usable wallet credential

Oracle DB Client -> Oracle Wallet Store: Write Oracle Net config
note  Oracle Wallet Store: drive: Oracle Net config resolves FREEPDB1_WALLET
sqlnet.ora and tnsnames.ora do not contain DB password

Oracle DB Client -> Oracle Wallet Store: Read wallet and Net config
note  Oracle DB Client: runtime: wallet credential is loaded into memory
note  Oracle Wallet Store: read: wallet credential for FREEPDB1_WALLET
read: Oracle Net config for database address

Oracle DB Client -> Oracle DB: Login as app_user using wallet credential
Oracle DB -> Oracle DB Client: Auth OK, user=APP_USER

Oracle DB Client -> Vault Agent: HTTP 200 OK
note  Oracle DB Client, Vault Agent: response: status ok, oracle_user APP_USER

Vault -> Oracle DB: Next scheduled DBSE rotation
note  Vault, Oracle DB: DBSE plugin runs ALTER USER with new Vault password

Vault Agent -> Vault Agent: Restart update-wallet.py
note  Vault Agent: Vault Agent restarts update-wallet.py after DBSE credential changes